Operatives of the Yobe State police command have arrested of one Ado Alhaji Kanwa for allegedly defiling an 18-month-old baby in Karasuwa local government area. The police announced the arrest of the suspect in a statement signed by the command’s spokesman, Dungus Abdulkarim. He said that the suspect was arrested after having molested and raped the baby, adding that the incident occurred in Karasuwa local government area. Abdulkarim said that the victim sustained various degrees of vaginal injuries as a result of the suspect’s act. According to him, investigation had since commenced for the subsequent prosecution of the suspect. The commissioner of police, Yahaya Sahabu Abubakar, appealed to members of the public to always report all forms of criminalities around them while going about their lawful duties. He also urged people in the rural areas to continue to work with the security agencies by giving them useful information in order to flush out criminals from the society.